LABEL: A rdfs:label
definition: A definition

LABEL: Canada
definition: Canada is a country that exists in north America.

LABEL: intradermal route
definition: A route of administration that inject the material(such as vaccines, allergens) into the skin itself.

LABEL: intragastric injection route
definition: An intragastric route that has a vaccine injection site located in stomach.

LABEL: intragastric route
definition: A route of administration that located in the stomach, so that the material is taken into body through stomach directly.

LABEL: intramuscular route
definition: A route of administration that inject the material(such as vaccines, allergens) directly into a muscle.

LABEL: intranasal route
definition: A rounte of administration that located in nose.

LABEL: intraperitoneal route
definition: A route of administration that located in the peritoneum.

LABEL: intravenous route
definition: A route of administration that is located in the vein

LABEL: oral route
definition: A route of administration that located in the mouth

LABEL: pharyngeal mucosal route
definition: Pharyngeal mucosal route is an oral route of administration.

LABEL: route of administration
definition: A path that is located in gross anatomical part of an organism (e.g., human) and is used for administering a vaccine, a drug, fluid, poison, or other substance into the body.
editor note: CDISC has a codelist: Rout of Administration. Desription from CDISC: The course by which a substance was administered in order to reach the site of action in the body. CDISC_SDTM_Route_of_Administration_Terminology

LABEL: subcutaneous route
definition: A route of administration that is loacted in the hypodermis (subcutaneous tissue) region.

LABEL: sublingual route
definition: An oral route of administration that is underneath the tongue.

LABEL: subtenon route
definition: A route of administration that is through the membrane covering the muscles and nerves at the back of the eyeball

LABEL: USA
definition: USA is a country that exists in north America.

LABEL: vaccination site
definition: The site that is the part of the host body and the entrance point where a vaccine is administered.
comment: it is not the natural anatomical part where the body has access toward outside, such as mouth or nose. But rather the holes on the skin made by needdles used for vaccination.

LABEL: vaccine injection site
definition: A vaccination site that is used for injection of a vaccine.

LABEL: intratumoral route
definition: A route of administration that inject the material (such as vaccines, allergens) directly into a tumor.

LABEL: intralesional route
definition: A route of administration that inject the material (such as vaccines, allergens) directly into a lesion or into the skin.
